51:03.018 --> 51:05.270
We all knew something was up,
we didn't know what.

51:05.270 --> 51:07.355
'Cause it was like,
he's trying to save the Loom,

51:07.355 --> 51:08.857
he gets the throne, all of this.

51:08.857 --> 51:11.943
But the problem was,
is that he didn't have the sacrifice

51:11.943 --> 51:15.113
<i>and we realized,
why doesn't he destroy the Loom</i>

51:15.113 --> 51:17.949
<i>and then have to take over
the Loom's massive responsibility?</i>

51:17.949 --> 51:19.534
<i>He doesn't get anything out of it.</i>

51:19.534 --> 51:22.913
<i>It seems so obvious now,
it seems like exactly the right choice.</i>

51:22.913 --> 51:25.832
<i>But that was a watershed moment
in the development of it,</i>

51:25.832 --> 51:29.169
<i>when we realized Loki needs
to destroy and become the Loom.</i>

51:29.169 --> 51:32.923
<i>We see
his normal clothes shed off</i>

51:32.923 --> 51:35.509
<i>and reveal his final Loki costume</i>

51:35.509 --> 51:37.594
<i>and his horns begin to grow back.</i>

51:40.806 --> 51:43.350
We've already shot Tom
climbing these stairs

51:43.350 --> 51:46.436
<i>and ascending to what will become,
effectively, his throne,</i>

51:46.436 --> 51:49.606
<i>as he then holds onto time
