<i>- beyond the self.</i>
<i>Right.</i>

53:52.938 --> 53:57.275
<i>And these are
the garments of purpose and practice.</i>

53:57.275 --> 53:59.277
<i>And weight.</i>
<i>And weight.</i>

53:59.277 --> 54:01.196
<i>- Yeah.</i>
<i>Yeah.</i>

54:01.196 --> 54:03.281
<i>Was it Mobius
who says in Episode 6,</i>

54:03.281 --> 54:06.743
"Sometimes purpose
is more burden than glory.

54:06.743 --> 54:08.453
"You choose your burden."

54:08.453 --> 54:10.956
And so, this is him
accepting that mantle.

54:26.012 --> 54:29.307
<i>The first ten years of movies
with Loki was about the glory.</i>

54:29.307 --> 54:31.977
<i>He was a villain,
he was chasing a throne.</i>

54:33.353 --> 54:36.273
<i>This season is about him learning
that his glorious purpose</i>

54:36.273 --> 54:38.942
<i>is to carry the burden
of everyone else.</i>

54:39.859 --> 54:42.821
<i>He's embracing the caring person
that he's turned into</i>

54:42.821 --> 54:44.739
<i>through these two seasons,</i>

54:44.739 --> 54:47.200
but he's also embracing his past

54:47.200 --> 54:50.245
<i>and his status as an Asgardian god</i>

54:50.245 --> 54:54.499
<i>to hold everything together
and to save his friends.</i>

54:54.499 --> 54:55.875
He's giving us a chance.

54:56.293 --> 54:59.504
His magical power as a demigod

54:59.504 --> 55:02.215
is enhanced because he realizes
that this...

55:02.215 --> 55:07.679
this authority he has
over coordinating and managing time

55:07.679 --> 55:09.723
<i>is, in fact, where the story ends.</i>

55:09.723 --> 55:15.645
<i>And it's his only resistance
